cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about improving abstractive text summarization using a neural sequence to sequence model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new mechanism to address the challenge of long text representation, which is a common problem in natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a Transformer model, which is a popular deep learning architecture for natural language processing tasks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as summarization is a common task in information retrieval and the paper evaluates the proposed model using ROUGE metrics, which are commonly used in summarization evaluation. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the proposed model is based on a neural network architecture.
